<div id="stitle" style="display:none;">Notebook Entry</div>
<dl id="n43093b"> <dt class="nbunit"><a name="n43" href="#n43093b">N43 (VI.B.35)</a>:  <a href="../../ff/fnbs/n43all.htm#n43093b"> 93(b)</a></dt> <dd> <blockquote> legit ut clericus</blockquote> <dd class="well"> <blockquote class="sources"><font color="green">[On benefit of clergy]</font> A prisoner sentenced to death might be claimed by the bishop of the diocese as a clerk and haled before him, wwhen the ordinary gave the man a Latin book from whioch to read a verse or two. If the ordinary said &ldquo;<mark>Legit ut clericus</mark>&rdquo;&mdash;<i>i.e.</i> &ldquo;he reads like a clerk&rdquo;&mdash;the offender was only burnt in the hand, and then set free. <small> Edward Clodd, <a name="ECSA2" href="../../ff/fdra/fdex.htm#ECSA2"><cite title="source">The Story of the Alphabet</cite></a>, rev. ed. (1913) 22 [Introductory]</small></blockquote> </dd></dl>
